    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="704"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 134.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s cable
                    instruction of yesterday requesting that I telegraph the full names of certain
                    Japanese officers and men captured May 2 and 3, while taking part in the Port
                    Arthur blockading party, and also of those taken prisoners when the <hi
                        rend="italic">Kinshu Maru</hi> was sunk, I have the honor to state that I
                    had already asked the ministry for foreign affairs to furnish me with the full
                    names of these officers and all of their fellow-prisoners, and that His
                    Excellency Count Lamsdorff had already caused a telegram to be sent to Admiral
                    Alexieff requesting that these names be telegraphed as soon as possible, and I
                    hope to receive them within a day or two.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert S. McCormick.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
